            = \n| demographics_type1              = Languages\n| demographics1_title1            = Official\n| demographics1_info1             = [[Marathi language|Marathi]], [[Hindi]]\n<!-- | Education_type          = Education\n| Education               = 77.66 (commented out as template does not contain this parameter) -->| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code                     = 413114<ref>{{cite web |title=Locate Post Office |url=https://www.indiapost.gov.in/VAS/Pages/LocatePostOffices.aspx?Pin=nPtgmA4fCMc= |website=indiapost.gov.in}}</ref>\n| area_code_type                  = Telephone code\n| area_code                       = 02111<ref>{{cite web |title=Locate Post Office |url=https://www.indiapost.gov.in/VAS/Pages/LocatePostOffices.aspx?Pin=nPtgmA4fCMc= |website=indiapost.gov.in}}</ref>\n| registration_plate              = \n| blank1_name_sec1                = \n| blank1_info_sec1                = \n| blank2_name_sec1                = \n| blank2_info_sec1                = \n| blank3_name_sec1                = \n| blank3_info_sec1                = \n| website                         = \n| iso_code                        = \n| footnotes                       = \n| official_name                   = \n}}\n'''Kadbanwadi''' (Devanagari: \u0915\u0926\u092c\u0928\u0935\u093e\u0921\u0940) is a [[village]] in the Indapur [[tehsil]] of [[Pune district]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]. It is located at a distance of 234 Km from the state capital [[Mumbai]]. The village is known for the water conservation initiatives taken by a resident, Pawar Bhajandas, whose efforts helped transform the village into a self-sufficient [[Gram panchayat|gram]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebetterindia.com/123663/water-conservation-kadbanwadi/|title=This Retired Teacher Transformed a Barren Village With Water Conservation!|last=Aranha|first=Jovita|date=7 December 2017|website=The Better India|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Agriculture==\nThis \u201cAdarsh Gram\u201d or model village is also famous for its [[polyhouse]] [[farming]]. As per the report of Agro Climatic, the village is a water scarcity zone in Maharashtra, with less than 400mm of rainfall per year. Most of the villagers used to feed shepherds and practice animal husbandry.  The forestlands have a great floral and faunal diversity.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebetterindia.com/123663/water-conservation-kadbanwadi/|title=This Retired Teacher Transformed a Barren Village With Water Conservation!|last=Aranha|first=Jovita|date=7 December 2017|website=The Better India|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Villages]]\n[[Category:Indian Villages]]\n[[Category:Maharashtra Villages]]\n[[Category:Pune District Villages]]\n[[Category:Villages in Indapur Tehsil]]\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Kadbanwadi\n| other_name                      = \n| nickname                        = \n| settlement_type                 = Village\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| pushpin_map                     = India Maharashtra\n| pushpin_label_position          = right\n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Maharashtra, India\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|18.0724794|N|74.8360918|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flagu|India}}\n| subdivision_type1               = State\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Maharashtra]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[Divisions of Maharashtra|Division]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Pune division]]\n| subdivision_type3               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name3               = [[Pune district|Pune]]\n| established_title               = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date                = \n| founder                         = \n| named_for                       = \n| government_type                 = \n| governing_body                  = \n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_rank                       = \n| area_total_km2                  = 27.66 \n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = \n| population_total                = 1636 <ref>{{cite web |title=Demographic |url=http://censusindia.gov.in/2011census/dchb/DCHB_A/27/2725_PART_A_DCHB_PUNE.pdf |website=censusindia.gov.in}}</ref>\n| population_as_of                = \n| population_rank                 = \n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_demonym              = \n| population_footnotes            = \n| demographics_type1              = Languages\n| demographics1_title1            = Official\n| demographics1_info1             = [[Marathi]], [[Hindi]]\n<!-- | Education_type          = Education\n| Education               = 77.66 (commented out as template does not contain this parameter) -->| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code                     = 413114<ref>{{cite web |title=Locate Post Office |url=https://www.indiapost.gov.in/VAS/Pages/LocatePostOffices.aspx?Pin=nPtgmA4fCMc= |website=indiapost.gov.in}}</ref>\n| area_code_type                  = Telephone code\n| area_code                       = 02111<ref>{{cite web |title=Locate Post Office |url=https://www.indiapost.gov.in/VAS/Pages/LocatePostOffices.aspx?Pin=nPtgmA4fCMc= |website=indiapost.gov.in}}</ref>\n| registration_plate              = \n| blank1_name_sec1                = \n| blank1_info_sec1                = \n| blank2_name_sec1                = \n| blank2_info_sec1                = \n| blank3_name_sec1                = \n| blank3_info_sec1                = \n| website                         = \n| iso_code                        = \n| footnotes                       = \n| official_name                   = \n}}\n'''Kadbanwadi''' (Devanagari: \u0915\u0926\u092c\u0928\u0935\u093e\u0921\u0940) is a [[village]] in the Indapur [[tehsil]] of [[Pune district]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]. It is located at a distance of 234 Km from the state capital [[Mumbai]]. The village is known for the water conservation initiatives taken by a resident, Pawar Bhajandas, whose efforts helped transform the village into a self-sufficient [[Gram panchayat|gram]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebetterindia.com/123663/water-conservation-kadbanwadi/|title=This Retired Teacher Transformed a Barren Village With Water Conservation!|last=Aranha|first=Jovita|date=7 December 2017|website=The Better India|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Agriculture==\nThis \u201cAdarsh Gram\u201d or model village is also famous for its [[polyhouse]] [[farming]]. As per the report of Agro Climatic, the village is a water scarcity zone in Maharashtra, with less than 400mm of rainfall per year. Most of the villagers used to feed shepherds and practice animal husbandry.  The forestlands have a great floral and faunal diversity.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebetterindia.com/123663/water-conservation-kadbanwadi/|title=This Retired Teacher Transformed a Barren Village With Water Conservation!|last=Aranha|first=Jovita|date=7 December 2017|website=The Better India|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Villages]]\n[[Category:Indian Villages]]\n[[Category:Maharashtra Villages]]\n[[Category:Pune District Villages]]\n[[Category:Villages in Indapur Tehsil]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toMarathi(link changed toMarathi language) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kadbanwadi"}
